-- Ex-Yankee Melky Cabrera Released by Braves After One Season With MLB Team
-- B y   E b e n   N o v y - W i l l i a m s
-- 2010-10-19T19:05:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/ex-yankee-melky-cabrera-released-by-braves-after-one-season-with-mlb-team.html
Melky Cabrera  was released by the
Atlanta Braves less than a year after being traded to the club
from the New York Yankees.  Cabrera, 26, batted .255 with a .317 on-base percentage and
four home runs this season. He made his Major League Baseball
debut with the Yankees in 2005 and became a fan favorite on June
6, 2006, when he reached over the outfield wall and stole a home
run from Boston Red Sox outfielder  Manny Ramirez .  Cabrera batted .154 in the Yankeesâ€™ 2009 World Series win
over the Philadelphia Phillies and was traded to the Braves in
the offseason in a deal that included pitcher  Javier Vazquez .  The Braves also released 40-year-old relief pitcher  Takashi Saito , team spokesman Brad Hainje said in a telephone interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
